

r.random - 

r.random allows the user to create a @glossary("raster",16.glossary/rastdata.def) map layer and a @glossary("sites",16.glossary/site.def)
list file containing geographic coordinates of points whose locations
have been randomly determined.  The program locates these
randomly-generated sites within the current @glossary("geographic region",16.glossary/georeg.def) and
@glossary("mask",16.glossary/mask.def), if any, on non-zero @glossary("category value",16.glossary/catval.def) data areas within a
user-specified raster map layer.

